ODM leader Raila Odinga and deputy party leader Hassan Joho are in Ghana for the inauguration of President-elect Nana Akufo-Addo.This comes as ODM plans a major meeting with aspirants.Raila left the country yesterday, hours after the Senate passed the controversial electoral laws, to attend Akufo-Addo&rsquo;s big day slated for today. Akufo-Addo, 72, a longtime opposition leader defeated incumbent John Mahama, 57, in historic polls that were held in December last year.&ldquo;While in Ghana, Raila and his delegation will meet sections of the new administration. He will return to Nairobi next week,&rdquo; Raila&rsquo;s spokesman Dennis Onyango said in a statement.Like Raila, Ghana&rsquo;s President-elect had lost prior runs for the presidency in 2008 and 2012.In 2012, the Supreme Court threw out his election petition against outgoing President John Mahama amid calls by his critics that he should retire from politics.The Star has also established that Raila will hold a critical meeting with all ODM aspirants in Nairobi upon return from Ghana.